  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1337220941" />
    <a title="Sandra (Crandomblog)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5456695-sandra-crandomblog"><img alt="Sandra (Crandomblog)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1333161537p2/5456695.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1337220941?book_show_action=true">Jul 16, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sandra (Crandomblog)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sandra (Crandomblog)" href="/user/show/5456695-sandra-crandomblog">Sandra (Crandomblog)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5456695-sandra-crandomblog?shelf=books-read-in-2015">books-read-in-2015</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1337220941" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6604315008990434042">I am a nerd, I have known this for a while, so when I got the chance to review this, I JUMPED at it! However, I wasn’t one hundred percent happy with it.<br/><br/>A warning, it is written in interview format. It is about a young female reporter who goes to interview the sole survivor from ‘our’ time. He is very condescending and very hard to actually like. He is very annoying and is a very big know-it-all in my opinion. The main reason I was excited about this was it was a novel that took place in the fut</span>
  <span id="freeText6604315008990434042" style="display:none">I am a nerd, I have known this for a while, so when I got the chance to review this, I JUMPED at it! However, I wasn’t one hundred percent happy with it.<br /><br />A warning, it is written in interview format. It is about a young female reporter who goes to interview the sole survivor from ‘our’ time. He is very condescending and very hard to actually like. He is very annoying and is a very big know-it-all in my opinion. The main reason I was excited about this was it was a novel that took place in the future. What killed that for me is while it does take place in the future, the majority of it is about our time (2015) and current issues and conspiracy theories.<br /><br />I did still kind of enjoy it though. It did open up your mind to new possibilities. It has made me think. Over all it was enjoyable and completely original. I would recommend it to anyone who is a fan of conspiracy theories and those fandoms listed on the back of the book (Fans of Babylon 5, Star Trek TNG, Battle Star Galactica (the new one) and classic science fiction writing). There were loads of easter eggs and the writing, though in an odd format, is stellar.<br /><br /> <br /><br />Sandra<br /><br />3.5/5 stars.<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.crandomblog.com/?p=476">http://www.crandomblog.com/?p=476</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="6604315008990434042" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
